main event: Two unidentified objects were sighted over Tachikawa & Yokata AFB, Japan on January 1, 1958.
interesting points: One object was a bright, flickering red object that moved up and down and was about 2-5 miles away.
The other object was a small, dim white object that moved at a fast, erratic speed and disappeared behind clouds about 1/2 mile away.
The objects were observed by air force personnel for around 3 minutes.
The report concludes the objects were probably meteors or balloons.
No photographs were included in the report.
